cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision and image processing, specifically predicting depth maps from RGB images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a standard encoder-decoder architecture, which falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of their method, which falls under the domain of statistical learning, making cs.LG a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with spatial structure and geometry, which falls under the domain of graphics and robotics, making cs.GR and cs.RO possible sub-categories.
